cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.DS, cs.MA, cs.AI 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it deals with investigating the spreading of information in online social media. It could also belong to cs.SOC (Computational Social Science) as it involves analyzing user interaction data from social media platforms. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it uses the independent cascade model to simulate spreading processes. It could also be classified under cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) as it involves analyzing the behavior of multiple agents (users) in a network. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves selecting the best seed selection strategy for information spreading.
